name: LUXURY APT NEW OPENING VIA DEL BABUINO
reviews:
['JohnFebruary 2020Everything we had hoped for and more!**', '**EmiliaDecember 2019The location was fabulous, a 5 minute walk from the Spanish steps. Lots of great restaurants very near to the house. Giuseppe was a great host, allowing us to drop our bags off early before check in. He also provided pastries upon check in that we enjoyed with coffee for breakfast. You won’t regret booking this place!**', '**IlyaDecember 2019Place is located right in the center near popolo square. 
Only minutes walking from the metro and some good places to snack. Unfortunately I think the restaurants are either too expensive or for tourists only without authentic good food.
There is somewhat of noise at night outside the windows from tourists lately but otherwise quiet.
Very good value for the money.**', '**RaulNovember 2019It’s a good place for a small family near or easy access to everything**', '**LouiseNovember 2019Great apartment in a great location. 20 minute walks to major sites. Even quicker by Metro which was very convenient. Close to supermarket. So many lovely restaurants on side streets near the apartment.  The apartment is on a lively street but it is quiet at night. 

We booked a day trip to Pompeii with City Wonders that conveniently left from Piazza Del Popolo, less than 5 minutes from the apartment. 

Giuseppe was a great host and very accommodating.**', '**MichelleOctober 2019The location is perfect for everything to do Rome. The host is a great communicator and arranged for our transportation from the airport. Just wonderful.  We would definitely stay again.**', '**']

name: Benalong Apartment  at Gladesville
reviews:
['PamelaJune 2019Beautiful place with lovely views!  So cozy and comfortable with gracious hospitality!**', '**NicolasJune 2020Super pleased. Great host. Great place. Amazing stay !**', '**NicolasMay 2020Only one word for this experience and that is PERFECTION !

I couldn’t ask for anything better thank you so much. Couldn’t be happier with this apartment honestly :)

Thank you !**', '**Zhen YiMarch 2020Upon our arrival, we were greeted with a very modern and clean apartment with complimentary fruits, snacks, drinks and is filled with small thoughtful touches around. The place is/looks just as amazing as the listing describes and we felt at home almost immediately.

The amenities provided were more than plenty for an enjoyable 2 week stay and the balcony offers a great view of the city skyline. While being in a fairly quiet neighborhood, the location of the apartment is very convenient with only a short walk to the supermarket, pharmacy and more.

Being our first booking on Airbnb, we had a wonderful experience both communicating with Misael and Filipa as well as our stay and would love to return in future trips back to Sydney.Upon our arrival, we were greeted with a very modern and clean apartment with complimentary fruits, snacks, drinks and is filled with small thoughtful touches around. The place is/… read more**', '**MarisaMarch 2020This apartment is a real gem. Located centrally in Gladesville it is a stylish place with great city views. On arrival there are snacks and drinks available which is a nice touch. The apartment is really clean with a great shower and all the amenities and appliances you need for a short or long stay.  The hosts are accessible if you have questions or need anything. The bed is comfortable and it is a safe apartment building. Close to shops, restaurants and transport.  My only suggestions for perfection would be instructions for the appliances and a ceiling fan in the bedroom. A great choice for a fantastic apartment in a nice neighbourhood close to the Sydney CBD.**', '**TessaFebruary 2020The flat is very conveniently located, a few minutes stroll to the shops and main road. It was a very modern, spacious flat, clean and nicely laid out ', ' completely the same as advertised (if not better). The host were very generous to provide complimentary snacks, coffee capsules, drinks etc. It definitely feels like a home away from home. 

The balcony was a true highlight as it is really big and has a very open and phenomenal view of the city skyline. As we were there in the height of summer, having the aircon was amazing. The building and area around the flat was very safe which was important as we had an elderly staying there so it was nice to see everything was very secure. We will definitely look to stay there again should we head to Australia!**', '**']

name: Studio Atman w/ Kitchenette in Conscious community
reviews:
['PatriciaJuly 2019We loved staying at Sha’s place!! The community is really what sets this location apart from the others in the San Pedro/San Jose area. Our neighbors were amazing and gave so many tips on the area and Costa Rica in general. This was our first time staying in Costa Rica and we were there for over a month, so having a community rather than just an apartment to rent really helped us to get settled and feel comfortable in the city.We loved staying at Sha’s place!! The community is really what sets this location apart from the others in the San Pedro/San Jose area. Our neighbors were amazing and gave so many… read more**', '**BlancaFebruary 2019I feel so fortunate to have found this magical place. It is so beautiful that I have decided to extend my stay longer and when I return to CR, I will return as this place has been more than what I expected.**', "**BlancaJanuary 2019Wow! What an amazing and special place...from the main house to the back where the beautiful garden is located. I really love this space and Sha's energy and hospitality. Both my daughter, 6 years old, and I love the entire Conscious Community concept that Sha has brought to life.  We are so happy here that we have extended our stay for the entire time that we will be in Costa Rica.  The top things that added to our positive experience at Sha's: Sha's beautiful energy, the garden, community dinners, community garden days, the diverse group of people who come from all walks, having hot water for showers,  and last but not least, Luna, Maya's favorite cat! I would highly recommend this special place. You will not want to leave !**", '**SarahOctober 2018I love the studio!  It was cute, clean, everything worked, has a view from the kitchen into a lush jungle garden.  The other people that live and stay here were also amazing.  There is something almost everyday to participate in from yoga to community dinners.  I’ll come again and again!**', '**RafaelAugust 2018The place is a small studio with a window view into the garden. It has a great feeling. As is in the back of the house is very quite. Kitchen has basics. Great location. Walking distance to San Jose’s center. Cora was a stupendous host. 
Got a complimentary yoga class.
If you like to travel frugal and heart I highly recommend this place.
The kitties and the dog are the sweetest.**', '**AlexanderJuly 2018Sha and the rest of the community were super helpful and attentive during our week', 'long stay. The studio was on the smaller side but clean and had everything we needed to cook our own meals. The bed was comfy and warm.

The house is ideally located near all amenities and buses that take you to downtown San José in little time. We loved discovering the area and the many vegan restaurants in it.

Things that could be improved: 
', ' The place was a bit hard to find. As there is no address system in Costa Rica, directions have to be given and in this case they were not totally clear.

', ' The bathroom could really use a hook to hang towels.

', ' The access to the back, where the studio was located had many obstacles (drying laundry, renovation materials, fallen fruit) in the hall and it was not well lit at night.

Overall our stay was positive and the three points mentioned above did not affect our general comfort level. We would stay again! Thank you!
**', '**']

reviews: ['NicoleMarch 2020Charles is a responsive and caring host who answers questions promptly. His apartment was clean. It is cosy and a bit small, but it is perfect for 2 people. It is in a safe location.Charles is a responsive and caring host who answers questions promptly. His apartment was clean. It is cosy and a bit small, but it is perfect for 2 people.  There are many, many s… read more**', "**EmilyOctober 2019Our stay in this apartment was mostly good, but we thought a few things could have been improved. It was in a really cool location. It was really easy to take the tram into the center of Brussels and we even walked once and it took about half an hour. There are tons of restaurants right around the apartment and when speaking to some locals, they recommended spending time in Ixelles, walking around the lakes, etc. If you are considering staying here, you should know that there are a lot of stairs. It's fine if you're able bodied, but it was a bit challenging with our suitcases, especially after walking around all day. Other than that, the apartment could have been cleaner. We were informed day of that the apartment wouldn't be ready and cleaned until 5pm and when we got there everything looked good, but as soon as we opened the fridge the entire apartment started to smell. We had to open the windows to make the smell go away. Overall, we enjoyed our stay because it was a cool place in a cool area, but we wish it was a bit cleaner.**", '**AaronAugust 2019Very nice stay, the steps take getting used to. name: Ocean view villa surrounded by rain forest
reviews: ["Noel & KatieMarch 2020Our group really enjoyed our stay and previous reviews really helped us have appropriate expectations. Everyone agreed we would be very glad to return to this house. We echo all the positives people describe, so my review is mostly to provide info we didn't have from the reviews that would have been helpful.  Naama, the host, was always very quick to respond to messages but utilizes a property manager for things during the stay.  The property manager was also responsive.  They communicate by text message.  My husband had international data turned on while traveling but if we hadn't it would have been difficult to coordinate check in.  We cooked most meals at the house and found the kitchen sufficient to do so.  Wifi was about 80% reliable.  At night (more than one night) the wifi cut out.  While the house guide provides some good info re local attractions be sure to use GPS when you get on the road.  Distances are not accurate from the house and since nothing has an address it can cause confusion. Thank you to Naama for sharing her home!Our group really enjoyed our stay and previous reviews really helped us have appropriate expectations. Everyone agreed we would be very glad to return to this house. We echo all th… read more**", "**AngelaFebruary 2020Excellent family vacation in Costa Rica, highlighted by staying in this beautiful home! Our family of four (2 adults+ 16 and 4 year old) enjoyed the stunning views and accommodations at Naama's. The house is very private and is surrounded by the sounds of the rainforest. The check", 'in and overall communication with property managers was quick and helpful. Cristina was always a text away with any questions about the property or activities. We especially appreciated the wildlife on property, amazing view, the pool, layout of home', 'so much natural light, laundry on premises, activity suggestions in area found in a binder at the home, and having a cooler to use for beach outings. The bugs were no big deal, and not an intrusion in to the home if you keep screens closed. The nearby beach, Playa Matapalo, was delightful and ended up one of our favorites. Strongly recommend the waterfall Eco Chantales, and rafting at Rafiki Safari lodge.**', '**KellyJanuary 2020Our stay at Naama’s house was wonderful. Her home is perfectly located, secluded and away from tourists but close enough to everything. Our favorite towns were Dominical and Uvita, both a short drive away. You will feel like a local in your own slice of paradise up in the mountains. Everything was very clean, beautiful and as pictured. We loved how private and quiet it was. Playa matapalo is just 5 minutes away and chances are you will have the beach to yourself. Plenty of great restaurants in the area, La Parcela was our favorite. Don’t go crazy planning every detail, just get to the house, relax and check out Naama’s binders in the living room with recommended beaches, waterfalls, restaurants and excursions. Don’t be intimidated by the bugs! Like anywhere in the world, as long as you keep the screens shut and clean up after yourself you won’t have any bugs inside the house. Due to the altitude, the air is much more comfortable by the house than down at sea level. Between the atmosphere and great ventilation of the house, the temperature was always pleasant. Her house managers Cristina and Eric were both very helpful in making our stay comfortable, both only a text message away. Prior to arriving, Naama arranged for us to have private chefs. She put us in touch with Sharon and Priscilla of TropicalTaste. We stayed in touch through email and planned all the appetizers, dinners and desserts before arriving. They offer diverse dishes, brought the necessary ingredients and all of the food was AMAZING. I highly recommend having them for your stay. Don’t hesitate to book Naama’s house, we felt very safe the entire time and loved our stay.**', '**LibbyJanuary 2020This stylish and modern home is perfectly situated to take advantage of amazing views from all rooms and the outdoor living space.  Naama was great at communicating, as was Christina, her property manager.  The home is beautiful and comfortable, but could use additional seating in living area and around the pool.  Location near the small\ntown of Matapao was perfect, very empty and beautiful beach without the crowds of Uvita and Domenical, easy access to al the area activities. Highly recommend!!**', '**MeganDecember 2019We don’t always leave reviews but in this case we wanted people to know that this is an exceptional experience. This house is Amazing! The space is just so well laid out. It could not have been more functional for what you want on your tropical vacation. The views were unbelievable. The AC and internet worked great. The water was clean and safe to drink and the washer/dryer and dishwasher made tidying up convenient. Our kids lived in the pool. The outdoor shower was great for washing the sand off after the beach. We loved it here more than dozens of rental homes we’ve stayed at all over the world. Thank you!**', '**ChalanciaNovember 2019The house it self was nice, only thing that got me was the hill (which it was stated that it was a hill but that hill to me was veryyyy dangerous and also THE BUGS I understand that we are in a forest but the bugs were everywhere.... the kitchen, bedroom, in the bed, bathroom, living room everywhere... (bugs as in ants, cockroaches, flying bugs) all kind... the pictures will make the house look very better even though it was old modern, the beds and everything overall it was fair for a square. If I was to visit back I wouldn’t stay again. Also the comforters on the bed were very old fashion and the mattress was caving in... but don’t listen to me give it a try you may feel different.**', '**']

name: GC 138 | Brand New Loft Ipanema
convenient room  close to metro station
reviews:
['DerekAugust 2018My friend and I were visiting the beautiful city of Montreal. Absolutely stunning in the winter but also famous for its spring and summers. The city blends nature, culture, architecture, and pluralism in a way I’ve never seen. We had watched a sunset at the beautiful Saint Joseph’s oratory on Mount Royale when we booked to stay with Florent. Staying with Florent was as the old cliché puts it, simply to good to be true. His place is very close by Mount Royale and within walking distance of some beautiful cafes and delicious food spots. Florent was incredibly accessible to us from the beginning of booking, communicating with us by phone answering any questions we had about the surrounding area. When we arrived he assisted us with parking which was available for free right behind his apartment and safe from any regulation. His apartment was beautiful, incredibly clean and well kept, and our private room was comfortable well furnished and spacious. He told us we could come and go as we pleased. After returning from a night of axe throwing, we sat down with Florent and his room mate and engaged in an incredibly colorful, hysterical, and informational chat for several hours. We were laughing so much and it was so much fun we didn’t want it to end. My only regret is that I forgot to ask for a selfie. Would recommend staying with Florent to any traveler who wants not only a great location and a beautiful place to stay but the feeling of welcome and comfort. He made us feel like dear friends and not at all strangers or guests in his home.My friend and I were visiting the beautiful city of Montreal. Absolutely stunning in the winter but also famous for its spring and summers. The city blends nature, culture, archite… read more**', '**AvaAugust 2018Clean, comfortable room. name: Delightfull Penthouse 3 in Copa
reviews:
['DerekFebruary 2020It was a fantastic stay Ney is an incredible host who genuinely cares about his guests wellbeing.**', '**JackMay 2019NOT SAFE! I canceled the reservation after my first night!
INSEGURO! Cancelei a reserva depois de uma noite só!

', 'First and foremost, the host’s profile is misleading. The host appears to be a woman named “Lucia,” when it is in fact only a middle', 'aged man named “Ney.” Ney wore nothing but a sunga (Brazilian', 'style speedo bathing suit) during the entirety of my brief stay.
', 'The apartment is marketed as a "entire apartment," when it is really just a room within an apartment that the host has boarded off. It is situated on the communal rooftop of the building. The only entrance locks from the outside. It only locks from the outside. This means that I could (and was, twice) be trapped on the roof if a tenant of the building locks the door after leaving the rooftop. This is a HUGE safety hazard, especially in the case of fire – I would be trapped on the roof of the building.
', 'There is a total of three locks in the apartment: two on the main door and one on the bedroom door. The two locks on the main door are both very simple and fragile. The top lock frequently fell apartment when opening the door. The lock in the bedroom, also weak, could only be locked/opened from the outside. This means that I could not lock myself into the apartment at night while I was sleeping. I actually tested the security of these locks and was able to open all of them with a knife.
', 'The host only has (Hidden by Airbnb) on his laptop; he does not own a cellphone (although he does have a landline, but it can only be called with a Brazilian phone carrier). This means he can only be contact when he is at his computer. This proved to be a problem as I could not contact the host on numerous occasions, such as the very first night when I was locked onto the rooftop.
', 'After canceling the reservation, the host was both aggressive, rude, and persistently messaging me, asking that I reactive the canceled reservation. The atmosphere became unpleasant.

As I have been living in Rio for a cumulative eight months over the past two years (and I have stayed at many Airbnbs during this time), I can confirm that this is not a good choice. It is the only Airbnb with which I have ever had a problem. I strongly urge you to reconsider booking a stay with "Lucia" who is actually "Ney."**', '**MaciejMarch 2020Good place to stay just at Copacabana. The owner is a really nice and helpful person**', '**MaritFebruary 2020Pro’s:
', ' Safe neighboorhood
', ' Affordable place to stay
', ' Trustworthy owners who appreciate your safety
', ' Good wifi
Con’s:
', ' Smell of mold in bathroom
', ' Ants
', ' Stonehard bed**', '**Ana SaraApril 2020Esse anúncio é uma farsa. Não é um apartamento inteiro, é um quarto com uma pia, um microondas, e uma torradeira que não funciona. A pia é feita com uma vasilha plástica. Não tem como fazer comida, pois não tem fogão. Ao lado do quarto tem um banheiro, que o chuveiro vc só pode deixar cair água durante 4 minutos e desligar e religar pra continuar o banho. 
Ou seja, é um quarto pequeno com saída independente, e está sendo alugada como se fosse um apartamento inteiro.  Falta de respeito e de verdade na hora de fechar com o cliente. Desrespeitoso. 
Não recomendo**', '**BrunaMarch 2020Fomos muito bem recebidos. A localização é ótima, perto da praia e perto de vários comércios.**', '**']

name: Apartment on a rooftop in Downtown, Cairo
reviews:
['EmilyMarch 2020I honestly can’t say enough good things about our experience with Asmhan! As far as the flat, it’s in a great location. We felt super safe, there are a ton or restaurants nearby, and it’s about a block from the M1. You have the entire rooftop (inside and outside) to yourself. It felt like home! And even better was Asmhan herself! We were there during record', 'breaking storms that resulted in power and water outages and she still managed to make it one of the best parts of our trip. Her mom cooked the most delicious food for us as pretty much the whole city was shut down and she checked in on us numerous times. I cant say it enough ', ' book this place!**', '**AdamMarch 2020I can not say enough positive things about Asmhan and her Airbnb!

Our flight arrived in Cairo at 3 am on a Sunday morning.. not only did Asmhan arrange a cab to pick us up, but she WAITED for us to arrive.

She has the best recommendations for the neighborhood and all of Cairo, ranging from restaurants to tourist sites. 

Her family is incredibly welcoming, her mother even cooked us dinner (which we regrettably couldn’t finish). 

This has been my best Airbnb experience in using the website for the past 3 years and using it on multiple continents. 

Also, wish the cat luck on her pregnancy.. we miss her already.**', '**SebastianFebruary 2020One of my best AirBnB experiences! Asmhan is such a kind and gracious host; she kept checking in with us throughout our stay if there was anything we needed and helped with airport pick', 'up, visits, and local recommendations. The rooftop apartment is located in a fantastic part of town and furnished in a stylish and unique way. 
I will definitely stay again during my next trip to Cairo. Highly recommended!**', '**AhmedJanuary 2020Asmhan’s place is in the heart of Cairo, Very clean and has a very nice view and little garden on the roof. Asmhan is very helpful and will kindly answer all your questions and will genuinely help you to have the perfect vacation.**', "**KarenJanuary 2020Asmhan's flat is perfectly located, clean, and lovely! The real treat is Asmhan herself, though. She is incredibly kind and helpful, aiding us in booking a tour/guide, finding places to eat and see, etc. She knows the area well and is an experienced & gracious host.**", '**MirriamDecember 2019If you are traveling to Cairo stay in this place. It is in a very nice location, a short walk to Tahrir square, easy for Uber’s to find you and so much to eat just in this location. This was, by far, the best experience I’ve had at an Airbnb and I think it’s the host that made the difference. Asmhan and her family are amazing ', ' her mom made us food and her brother delivered it. One night I had popcorn and feta salad with fresh bread. Another night homemade koshary. She is so quick to respond to any comment and had helpful tips on where to go and what to see and eat. It’s a great value in a hectic city and oh yes there’s the flat cat! She’s the best Cairo kitty ever.**', '**']

name: Mirador Las Golondrinas
reviews:
['WilliamJune 2020Warm hearts and a great view.**', '**EricMarch 2020Maria and Felt x are wonderful hosts with a beautiful home. It sits atop a mountain where both sunrises and sunsets can be taken in each day. Three volcanoes can also be seen from the kitchen!

As hosts, Maria and Felix did everything possible to make sure our stay was enjoyable. Maria had great tips for things to do and restaurants to eat at. The waterfall, only 20 minutes from their house, was an amazing find.Maria and Felt x are wonderful hosts with a beautiful home. It sits atop a mountain where both sunrises and sunsets can be taken in each day. Three volcanoes can also be seen from… read more**', '**CesarFebruary 2020Five star host! 
The place is gorgeous, clean, very well maintained. 
I loved my stayed and I’ll definitely stay there again.**', '**Hang', 'NgaJanuary 2020Wonderful! Beyond all my expectations. Maria and her husband were so gracious and welcoming. We had a difficult time locating their place', ' HINT (Hidden by Airbnb) Maps is 50/50 in Costa Rica at best. Felix had to drive out and escort us back to their location and after we dropped our bags off, they were the best of hosts to drive us around San Pedro to get us better acquainted with the lay out of the town and dropped us off to a fabulous local seafood spot in town and delivered us back. If Maria and Felix are not enough to convince you that this is best stay you can ask for', " let me tell you about our decision to book this space before meeting Maria and Felix.
This was our first trip to Costa Rica and we were celebrating our 25th anniversary, so I was tempted to splurge a little and check at Blanca Villa in the Los Angeles Cloud Forest, but in the end in reading the reviews for Maria's place which miraculously was available", ' I really felt that we were more Airbnb type than resort type', " I've never been so pleased to be absolutely right. 
Maria's place is atop a hill and is apart of Felix's family history. There are four generations currently residing in the area. The best part is that atop this hill is the Cloud Forest. I woke the first morning to be mesmerized by the swirling clouds just outside our picture windows. I must have spent an hour just emerged in that wonderous existence. Then to make things even better Maria offered us breakfast service (for a more than reasonable fee) and I had the first black coffee ever and it was so delicious. 
We did end up visiting the Los Angeles Cloud Forest (40 mins drive from here)  and it would have fallen short of what we were able to experience at Maria's place. Yes,  there were hikes and the site was beautiful but we would have been bored after the first day. With Maria's place there was the town right at foot of the hill to explore with wonderful locals to meet. There are day trips to volcanos, coffee plantations and so much more. 
The only thing to be aware of is that the wind does howl through the house", " but that's such a small price to pay for the luxury of experiencing the Cloud Forest setting. 
We met Maria and Felix's sons and they speak excellent English and are well mannered and charming young adults. Felix was so sweet that when he heard how much I loved the coffee he gifted me some. I feel our stay afforded us a great stay and new friends.**", '**MandyFebruary 2020This is a stunning apartment with spectacular views! After a month travelling in Costa Rica I wanted to splurge a little, and this place exceeded my expectations and was totally luxurious. It’s even lovelier than the pictures. Everything is stylish and comfortable (fluffy towels, even dressing gown and slippers!) and fully equipped to take care of all your needs. It even has Alexa for music! And a super, well equipped kitchen space for cooking. The views over San Ramon are first class. You have sunrise from the main bedroom and a lovely sofa area outside the room for taking in sunset. Absolutely glorious! The garden is really pretty too with places outside to sit in the small forest or on the porch. The guest suite is basically an annex of the main house so you have total independence and privacy with your own entrance. A communal laundry room separates the annex/suite from the main family house, so you have the best of both worlds with the family right next door whenever you need anything. And both Maria and Felix are first rate, exemplary hosts. They were both so warm, welcoming and engaging (even though my Spanish was very poor) and they went above and beyond what I expected, helping me out in many ways and always quick to communicate and offer suggestions. It’s an easy walk into town ', ' but conserve some energy for the return, as the last 5 minutes of the walk up the path to the house is very steep. But your reward is the magnificent vistas at the top! My taxi cost just under 2000 colones so it’s a cheap option if you prefer to take the easy way home! All in all, fantastic value for money. You will love it here!**', '**MarianFebruary 2020Exemplary hosts. We were given clear instructions on how to find the house and greeted on arrival. The property, which has breathtaking views in all directions, is beautifully designed and decorated and includes convenient and secure parking. We had everything we needed and were given valuable advice on local attractions and restaurants. The self', 'contained apartment is spacious, comfortable, clean and well', 'equipped. Thank you again to our charming and friendly hosts!**', '**']

Private, cozy garden unit near GG Park/UCSF
Gianicolo house  La terrazza delle meraviglie
reviews:
["JudyOctober 2019I couldn’t wait to share our love of this little apartment and our sweet host, Miki. She, along with her sister and mother, went over and above in order to make our stay comfortable. The night we went out to dinner for our anniversary, she drove us and, along with her sister, gave us a tour of the area with fabulous views you won’t get on any scheduled tour. The terrace is fabulous!  I would've lived out there if I could.  Buses are very handy, and if you stay here, you’ll feel absorbed in a true Italian neighborhood and not just surrounded by other tourists at a hotel. Oh, and did I mention the walls of the apartment sparkle?  Choose to stay here!**", '**LucaSeptember 2019We have been hosted one week in the cozy flat of Micaela and in the beatiful terrace...we had a great time and we will come back very soon. .thanks very much Micaela!**', '**AndyJuly 2019We (two adults and two teenagers) had a pleasant stay in this cute flat. It was very well equipped (including breakfast, full fridge, toilet utilities, etc) and for visiting Rome in the summer ideal. It was comparatively small in the inside but it was more than  made up for by the huge terrace where we enjoyed the weather and had breakfast. Excellent hosts and attentive to every detail.**', "**NourJuly 2019The booking was fast and very convenient, i had fast responses and we were able to make the best solution together for my stay.

I was planning to show my mother the best of rome and its surroundings, Micaela's marvelous roof balcony was the spot to stay.

Micaela was on time for the check in, she prepared a nice welcome treat and explained everything covering every detail.

The house was sparkling clean, it was outstanding how the appartment had everthing you might need for a warm house feeling in very well organized way.

She even prepared all the details needed for public transportation the house was close to a line that start next to it and ends in the very center of rome (20", '40min) depend on what time you depart.

The neighborhood was quite and had everything close to it, a coffee shop, a good typical restaurant and many supermarkets close to it.

I rented a car so i could go outside rome and the private parking spot under the house was a bonus.

The park next the house is very roman authentic(must visit)

Micaela was very fast responsive and very helpful, she guided us through everything gave us many tips and i had a health issue and she was there to helps us without problems.

It was my best airbnb experience by far. And the value for the money perfect.**', '**RobJune 2019A great bijou apartment with a fantastic roof terrace. Central Rome and the Vatican 15', '20 mins by tram or bus 1.5 Euro each way.
The host was very thoughtful and helpful. **', '**MarjorieOctober 2018We had a wonderful stay. The highlight is the terrace, it is so spacious and many different seating areas. Micaela’s mother checked us in and then escorted us around town to show us where everything was, grocery, restaurants, transit etc.. Getting to the city center was very easy, many options available.**', '**']

name: Cozy Suite of Downtown NYC 18mins to Timesquare
reviews: ['Elle LMay 2020Have stayed here multiple times..each stay is great!**', '**Elle LApril 2020Amazing hosts, awesome apartment, great location and little nuances in the apartment that make it all the more great to stay at. Location, incredible.**', '**IsaiApril 2020The check', "in was really easy and the place was really nice. The stove wasn't working when we were there, hopefully it gets fixed soon. If the appartment is full, you might be lucky and get quiet roommates.**", "**MelanieFebruary 2020The Good:  Stella's place is in a great location, just a block and a half from the Delancey/Essex Metro stop. It was very convenient to get to anywhere we wanted to go. There is an excellent Venezuelan restaurant a couple of doors down (Patacon Pisao) and a good Greek restaurant very nearby. We took the short walk to Chinatown twice. The place was also clean with no evidence of any bugs or vermin. The bathroom was roomy. I was pleasantly surprised to see that the rooms we booked both had full", 'sized beds (one of the rooms looked like it had a twin in the photo). There were lots of toiletries in the bathroom. Both of our bedrooms had separate locks and keys. The beds were comfortable, and the temperature was just right.\nThe Bad:  The main thing, and the reason I would not stay here again, is that the main door to the apartment has two locks that can only be locked/unlocked from the inside. Because of this, we were locked out twice in our 5', "night stay. One of the locks can be set very easily, and I believe the housekeeper set it when she was there for security but did not unset it when she left. Luckily, both times, there was someone else inside the apartment to let us in. If no one had been inside the apartment, there would've been no way for anyone to get in without removing the door or the doorknob. Other small inconveniences:  The apartment has no coffee pot. The wi", "fi didn't work. Stella said it worked for the housekeeper, but it didn't work on my device or my friend's, so I believe the password posted on the refrigerator was wrong. There was only one washcloth and one hand towel for the entire apartment (of three separately", "rented areas). There were extra bath towels, but no extra wash cloths or hand towels. We did ask for some, but it seemed like there was a language barrier, and we never received any (although we asked for and received a roll of paper towels). I wasn't bothered by the noise of any other guests, but I could hear people going up and down the stairs outside the apartment, especially on Saturday night.The Good:  Stella's place is in a great location, just a block and a half from the Delancey/Essex Metro stop. It was very convenient to get to anywhere we wanted to go. There is an… read more**", '**JinFebruary 2020we had a good experience indeed**', '**KarinaJanuary 2020Stella’s place is very nice. It is in a great location that is close to all of the main attractions in NY and their is a subway station down the street! I would recommend staying here!**', '**']

name: Elevated Sun Trap One Bedroom Apartment Herne Bay
reviews:
['KevinFebruary 2020Lovely view across the harbour, close to the beach, and beautiful neighborhood. Apartment is clean, well', 'appointed, and easily accessible.**', '**JeronimoJuly 2019Great place to stay. Very comfy and sparkling clean. Great location too. I would definitely stay again!**', "**MeganFebruary 2019Jan and Bill's place is a lovely apartment that will make you feel at home for whatever duration of stay you have in mind. (I just stayed there for 6 weeks while I was working at the University of Auckland.)

The location is perfect if you want to be just outside the main city of Auckland but within easy reach of the center. It takes not much more than 30 minutes to walk into the heart of the city, and there are also regular buses to take you there. Herne Bay itself is delightful. An easy walk along Jervois Road takes you to the busier area of Ponsonby Road. Herne Bay is more laid back and replete with great restaurants and coffee shops.

Jan and Bill are wonderful hosts and excellent communicators. I couldn't recommend them more highly.**", '**JulieAugust 2018I love to staying here. It was so cozy and welcoming.  Check in was a breeze and Jan and Bill were very responsive hosts. The only thing that I would mention is if you are going to take a taxi service from the airport to the apartment make sure that the driver is taking you to address number 39 unit 11. I discovered that the address is formatted correctly but when taxi drivers use (Hidden by Airbnb) to find it it tells them to go to street number 11.
In the evenings I would wrap myself in a blanket and turn the electric heater on and watch television and just relax on the couch. Then I would move the  heater into the bedroom and close the door and my bedroom was toasty warm for when I went to sleep. Also a nice touch for the colder winter weather was an electric mattress pad heater. Very comfortable bed and quality linens.
The bathroom was really nice and also had a washer and dryer for use. The shower was excellent. Strong water pressure and really hot water.
I loved being able to look out the windows and see the beautiful Herne Bay and the sunsets. Being on the top floor always s plus for me. 
The neighborhood is quaint and safe. The the taxi driver remarked to me "oh wow you're staying in a really nice neighborhood" when he dropped me off.
Catching the bus was easy. There's a bus stop close by.  I rode the bus almost everyday to the CDB. It was only $3.50 each way.  There are many restaurants, local businesses and even an excellent Chinese take away place all on the main road. There's also a small grocery store on that same street but I had no problem finding everything that I needed for 8 days to eat.
A really nice touch was finding fresh fruit and milk waiting for me when I arrived.
The only thing that I would add to the kitchen tools would be a dish rack to put freshly washed dishes in to dry. I used a towel and then leaned the dishes one on top the other so that they would dry overnight.
I had a wonderful stay at this apartment. I would definitely stay again in the future. Actually I wish I didn't have to leave it. It was starting to feel like home to me. :)**', '**MichaelMarch 2017Jan and Bills place is in an ideal location....walk to beach and great restaurants. Home had everything we needed and bed is super comfy!**', '**ChristianeMarch 2020The apartment is very clean and tidy. The area is very quiet and you have everything around.**', '**']

reviews: ['MingshanFebruary 2020We stayed for two weeks in Lina’s comfortable apartment. name: Brussels rooftop
reviews: ['StefanieApril 2019Samuel met us at the door to receive our keys, and was very nice and polite. Unfortunately, that was the best part. Upon arrival, there was paper in the toilet and hair clogging the drain when we went to take a shower. The place seems a bit of a mess and unorganized. The reason we booked was for the rooftop view, but scaffolding was on the private balcony and worker men where dragging building utensils on the balcony anywhere from 9am to 8pm at night, so we felt there was little privacy. The curtains do not close, so many times the men were just looking inside. The worker men on the roof drove us mad so we had to leave to get some quiet. The walls are very thin and you can hear EVERYTHING from the neighbors. Samuel is a nice guy but this was not what we expected.Samuel met us at the door to receive our keys, and was very nice and polite. Unfortunately, that was the best part. Upon arrival, there was paper in the toilet and hair clogging th… read more**', '**TrevorJune 2018It is a very small place, however for me and my girlfriend that were only visiting for one day to take in some sights around Brussels it was perfect! Very close to public transport but also close enough to walk to things. Apartment was very clean and he left us some wine and beer in the fridge. Checking in was really easy as was finding the place. Not to mention the great view from. The spacious balcony after a long day of walking around Brussels.It is a very small place, however for me and my girlfriend that were only visiting for one day to take in some sights around Brussels it was perfect! Very close to public transport… read more**', '**EllenMay 2018This was a very cheap place and Samuel was very quick to respond which was great however the place could use a thorough cleaning especially in the bathroom. I have stayed in 30 airbnb rentals and this was the dirtiest one upon arrival.  It was only $50 per night so I decide it was not worth complaining about after a long day of travel but I would expect the toilets to be cleaned, the shelves to be dusted, and the old towel to be removed from the bathroom. I would also expect the pile of old shoes not to be the first thing you see when you arrive in the small studio. The balcony had a great view but the photos do not show that there are rundown particle board shelves on the balcony that are not appeasing to the eye as well as used bottles and an old washing machine being used for a garbage bin that would benefit from cleaning the lid.  The linens for the sofa bed had a small blanket which was not large enough for two people so I would recommend if the apartment is meant for two people to get a queen size duvet and comforter or two duvets/comforters.  If you are able to get past the cleanliness it is in a good location with a good view and we did appreciate the early check in although Samuel was not available to meet us at check in or checkout.  I normally will put minor issues in a private note but I just want people to manage their expectations on the possible cleanliness state of the apartment.  I overlooked the previous review as someone being very particular about cleanliness but she/he was pretty accurate on the condition of the apartment.This was a very cheap place and Samuel was very quick to respond which was great however the place could use a thorough cleaning especially in the bathroom. I have stayed in 30 air… read more**', '**ShaunMarch 2018Loved the place, Samuel was wonderful! Cozy and close to where we wanted to be.**', '**JeremiahMarch 2020Nice place to stay!**', "**CristinaFebruary 2020The flat was comfy and warm. You have a lot of markets around and the neighbourhood is safe. It's kinda far away from a metro station but you have bus instead which it's fine.**", '**']

reviews:
['JoseMarch 2020Great place to stay and great hospitality from Alex/may; definitely recommend  it.

JM**', '**LynneMarch 2020This apartment was a little gem in the middle of the historic center of Mexico City. As first time travelers to Mexico City this was a very good neighborhood to be in as it was walking distance to the Zócalo and the pedestrian malls which had an abundance of stores and restaurants. And street entertainment which was very pleasant. The building is very nicely restored but the historic charm is kept in the lobby. The apartment itself is very modern and compact but plenty large enough for two people. The furnishings were modern and comfortable. reviews:
["MichaelFebruary 2019Great small apartment in a suburb of Tokyo. It takes approximately 45 minutes to get downtown, but I love the local feel of the place. It's a great place to get away from the crowds of Tokyo. It is located 4 minutes walk from a supermarket and 5 minutes walk from a local onsen/bath.Great small apartment in a suburb of Tokyo. It takes approximately 45 minutes to get downtown, but I love the local feel of the place. It's a great place to get away from the crowd… read more**", '**HaoDecember 2018Good place to stay. This place might be a little small for 2 people with big luggages to unpack. Room WiFi available, no pocket WiFi for travel.**', '**TysonOctober 2018I’ve been staying in a long term hostel in Shinjuku. I needed a break from the madness of Shinjuku and the people in my dormitory. This was exactly what I was after.

It’s in a residential area about 45 minutes from Shinjuku by train. Easy to get to. The area was quiet. The comforter and pillow were comfortable. I would stay again if I needed to get away.I’ve been staying in a long term hostel in Shinjuku. I needed a break from the madness of Shinjuku and the people in my dormitory. This was exactly what I was after.

It’s in a res… read more**', "**KyleOctober 2018Step into the front entrance, slip off your shoes, and there's the bathroom ", ' proximity itself a convenience. The entire room seems to have been made of round, gray', 'beige precision', 'molded sanitary plastic perfectly crafted in 1983 and kept impeccably clean since ', " there's a drain in the floor, space to put your toothbrush, and then you can grab the soap and take a shower. You turn the faucet on (it goes harder than you'd think, and a little goes a long way) and adjust the temperature before turning the little nozzle sticking out of the spout, diverting water to the shower head, it comes out with a LOT of pressure if you turn the things up. It also gets really hot. When you look at the walls of the shower, you realize that this is really a gigantic one", "person bathtub with a shower head. You can bathe, you can shower, you can have a secret adventure like you're five years old again ", " whatever you want. It was definitely the best shower/bath experience I have ever had on any trip I've taken so far on here. No matter how much money someone spends on a bathroom, what really matters is whether or not you can get yourself hosed down and ready to either go to bed or go outside for the day: and this bathroom lets you do that, easily, with a level of no", "frills precision that I haven't seen or felt in a long time. The soap, shampoo and conditioner Fang was nice enough to provide were incredible. Also, the toilet has a large/small flush power selector. It's the kind where you have to hold it for a few seconds until you feel it go. There's a ton of good (soft, yet sturdy) toilet paper available, and since the toilet is literally right where the tub is, you're always going to be as clean as you need to be. After you get out of the bathroom, the kitchen is right there too, in case you need to grab a drink, or something from the fridge, or if you want to cook something ", " there's a single", "burner gas stove! Make sure you take care of your trash, too, by the way: there's a nice poster on the inside of the door that tells you what days of the week and how many times per month they come by to pick up whatever kinds of trash, and what kind of bag it can be in and all kinds of stuff. You have to either follow this rule exactly by law or take all your trash out with you when you leave the apartment, so be aware of what to do in both cases ", " you'll find this anywhere in Japan if you aren't staying in a hotel, but just in case you didn't know that already, it makes sense to mention it here. Entering the living room, you'll see two long soft beds, both with ample power outlets (2", "prong; bring a 3P adapter, go to Yodobashi) and shelving, and if you look above you'll discover the ceilings are ridiculously tall ", '', ' possibly up to 4.5 meters high ', '', " and above you, what you thought was the ceiling of the entire house actually ended up being the floor above you, running the entire length of the house: an absolutely enormous loft. There was no ladder, at the time when I was there, but there would easily be enough room to sleep several people on futons if it was still set up as the traditional bedroom configuration. The real ceiling of the apartment isn't very high off that second floor, though: you'd be kneeling or crouching or crawling, depending on how tall you are, so there's no real use being up there. So, right now, it's being used for storage: but there's more than enough room to store things like your luggage and any larger items. This is, first and foremost, a place to sleep and recharge, for one or two people, before heading out for the day. If you have a laptop or tablet, use it: Fang has graciously provided free wifi, and it's fast. There's a small fridge to store your drinks and leftovers, and the place is sturdy and soundproof. I know this because there was a typhoon going on outside, Typhoon #24, and with 42mph winds I didn't hear or feel a thing until I stepped outside out of curiosity and saw/heard a street sign being ripped away and rolling down the street. Luckily, you're in the lee of the building ", '', ' so you won't be pelted by tons of wind and stuff while you're at the door. So I stepped back and went back to bed, and slept like a baby, without hearing a thing outside. My point here is, you don't have to worry about anything other than whatever you're doing on your trip in Japan, because Fang's apartment let me get in the door, noodle around on the internet for a few hours, and go to sleep before getting up the next day to do other things. That's ideally what any accommodations should be like. So here's how to do things: if you want to get to Akihabara, Ueno or any other major city in Japan: head towards Sugamo, then switch to the JR Yamanote line and head towards Tokyo Station, where you can go anywhere else in Japan (Shinkansen to any other major cities). If you have the JR Pass, like I did, you can easily just go anywhere else in the country on a whim within hours and then spend the entire day there, if you wake up early enough in the morning (if you consider 5am "early"). I went to Kyoto for the day one day and spent like 12 hours there before coming back and spending another 4 hours in town in Tokyo, and I didn't even get up to leave THAT early. But once again, at this point, you're already out...Step into the front entrance, slip off your shoes, and there's the bathroom ', ' proximity itself a convenience. The entire room seems to have been made of round, gray', 'beige precision… read more**', '**RuthAugust 2018Good place to stay at for the price. Everything was just as described and the place was clean with amenities. There is a nice park a few minutes of a walk from the place as well as a convenience store and supermarket.**', '**JorgeAugust 2018The best!**', '**']
